cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a spiking neural network based region proposal network, which is a clear indication of the involvement of neural computing. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The proposed algorithm is tested on traffic scene recordings from a DAVIS sensor setup, which is a clear indication of the involvement of computer vision. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed architecture consists of refractory, convolution and clustering layers designed with bio-realistic leaky integrate and fire (LIF) neurons and synapses, which is a clear indication of the involvement of machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed algorithm is based on spiking neural networks, which is a clear indication of the involvement of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - The proposed algorithm is tested on traffic scene recordings from a DAVIS sensor setup, which is a clear indication of the involvement of robotics.
